The paper deals with approximation algorithms for graph problems, specifically edge expansion and sparsest cut with product demands, on directed hypergraphs. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as well as computational geometry (cs.CG) since hypergraphs can be seen as a generalization of graphs and have applications in geometric algorithms. The paper also involves optimization and approximation techniques, which are relevant to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of an SDP formulation and primal-dual framework suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
